The following table details the IPC-S 
consumer prices report from the Getulio Vargas Foundation in 
Rio de Janeiro.  The IPC-S index monitors prices in  Brazil ’s 12 
biggest cities.   NOTE: Cities are weighted according to population.  Each collection
period is 30 days.  A basket of approx. 450 goods and services are 
represented for families whose incomes range from minimum wage to 33
times minimum wage.   SOURCE: Fundação Getúlio Vargas (FGV)  To contact the reporter on this story:
